A Brief Overview
Founded in 1538, the University of Debrecen has evolved into one of the leading educational institutions in Central Europe. Situated in the heart of Debrecen, Hungary's second-largest city, the university boasts a picturesque campus that blends historic architecture with modern amenities. With over 30,000 students from around the world, the university fosters a vibrant and multicultural learning environment.

Academic Excellence
At the University of Debrecen, academic excellence is at the forefront of everything we do. Our comprehensive range of undergraduate, graduate, and doctoral programs span a wide array of disciplines, including medicine, engineering, humanities, natural sciences, and social sciences. With the guidance of Qadri International Educational Consultants, students can navigate the admissions process with ease and confidence, ensuring they find the perfect program to pursue their academic interests and career aspirations.

